#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:103
msgid "Why on earth are we paying twice for the same electrons?"
msgstr "¿Por qué demonios pagamos dos veces por los mismos electrones?"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:105
msgid ""
"\n"
"    On bright days the peninsula often makes more solar than the local "
"grid can swallow. Instead of\n"
"    using every electron we grew for free, we leave it on the table while"
" other kit keeps running—\n"
"    and households foot the bill for flexibility twice. Politely put: "
"that should embarrass us.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    En los días claros la península a menudo produce más solar de la que "
"la red asimila cerca. En vez de\n"
"    usar cada electrón que nos regaló el cielo, lo dejamos en el aire "
"mientras sigue otro parque encendido—\n"
"    y las familias pagan la flexibilidad dos veces. Dicho fino: debería "
"darnos vergüenza.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:112
msgid ""
"\n"
"    <strong>What would actually help?</strong> Grids and storage we stop "
"talking about and start building,\n"
"    plus price signals that pay people to use clean power when the sun is"
" generous. Less waste, lower\n"
"    bills, fewer excuses. We know what to do.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    <strong>¿Qué ayudaría de verdad?</strong> Redes y almacenamiento de "
"los que dejemos de poner en PowerPoint y empecemos a construir,\n"
"    más señales de precio que paguen a la gente por usar limpio cuando el "
"sol es generoso. Menos despilfarro,\n"
"    facturas más sanas, menos excusas. Sabemos qué hacer.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:121
msgid "City-sized anger"
msgstr "Mal humor a escala de ciudad"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:123
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Today’s pile of unused solar is in the same league as the daily use "
"of about\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> ordinary homes (illustrative %(kwh)s kWh "
"per home per day—not a census,\n"
"    see methodology). That’s not abstract; that’s kitchens and lights "
"someone could have run for free.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El montón de solar no aprovechado de hoy va en la misma liga que el "
"consumo diario de unas\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> casas corrientes (ilustrativo %(kwh)s kWh "
"por hogar—no es censo,\n"
"    ver metodología). No es un abstracto: son cocinas y luces que alguien "
"podría haber encendido casi gratis.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:132
msgid "Methodology"
msgstr "Metodología"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:134
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The waste you see is real enough to measure—which is the infuriating "
"part. Quarter-hourly unused\n"
"    solar (MWh) comes from Red Eléctrica de España (REE) data, then "
"through a separate pipeline into\n"
"    this project’s database: rows keyed by date_day with qh_1_mwh through"
" qh_100_mwh (15-minute buckets).\n"
"    Same calendar day, multiple rows: we sum buckets before showing "
"anything.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El despilfarro que ves es lo bastante real para medirlo—y esa es la "
"parte que enfada. La energía solar no utilizada\n"
"    por cuartos de hora (MWh) sale de datos de Red Eléctrica de España "
"(REE), pasa por otra canalización y acaba\n"
"    en la base de este proyecto: filas por date_day con qh_1_mwh a "
"qh_100_mwh (cuartos de 15 minutos).\n"
"    Mismo día, varias filas: sumamos cubos antes de enseñar nada.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:142
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The chart aggregates those quarter-hours into 24 hourly bars "
"(Europe/Madrid calendar day). Any slots\n"
"    beyond the first 96 are folded into the last hour of the day. Day "
"totals are the sum of all\n"
"    quarter-hour values. “So far this year” uses SUM(total_mwh) across "
"rows from 1 January through the\n"
"    selected date. The average “per hour” figure is the mean of the 24 "
"hourly bars (equivalently the\n"
"    day total divided by 24).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El gráfico agrega esos cuartos de hora en 24 barras horarias (día "
"natural Europa/Madrid). Los huecos\n"
"    más allá de los primeros 96 se incorporan a la última hora del día. "
"Los totales del día son la suma de\n"
"    todos los cuartos. “Lo que llevamos de año” usa SUM(total_mwh) entre "
"filas del 1 de enero hasta la fecha\n"
"    elegida. La media “por hora” es la media de las 24 barras (equivale a"
" total del día / 24).\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:151
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Euro figures only appear if WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH is set: a blunt "
"illustrative rate × energy,\n"
"    not a market invoice—still useful for remembering this isn’t “free” "
"in anyone’s pocket.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Los importes en euros solo salen si WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH está "
"definido: un tipo ilustrativo bruto × energía,\n"
"    no una factura de mercado—sirve igual para recordar que esto no es "
"«gratis» para nadie.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:156
msgid "Household analogy"
msgstr "Analogía con hogares"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:158
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The household comparison uses a configurable illustrative kWh/day "
"figure to give an intuitive\n"
"    scale; replace or calibrate it when you publish official assumptions."
"\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    La comparación con hogares usa un valor ilustrativo de kWh/día "
"configurable para dar una escala intuitiva;\n"
"    sustitúyelo o calíbralo cuando publiques supuestos oficiales.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:166
msgid "Credits"
msgstr "Créditos"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:168
msgid ""
"\n"
"    This site was directly inspired by\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Este sitio se inspiró directamente en\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:171
msgid "Wasted Wind"
msgstr "Wasted Wind"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:172
msgid ""
"\n"
"    a data project by Robin Hawkes about wasted wind energy in Great "
"Britain. I am grateful for that work as a model for explaining curtailed "
"renewables in a clear, public-facing way.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    un proyecto de datos de Robin Hawkes sobre energía eólica "
"desperdiciada en Gran Bretaña. Le agradezco ese trabajo como modelo para "
"explicar renovables vertidas de forma clara y accesible.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:179
msgid "About"
msgstr "Acerca de"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:181
msgid ""
"\n"
"    I built Wasted Sun on my own time, because watching good solar go to "
"waste is maddening—and I’d\n"
"    rather show the numbers than swallow them. It is not an official "
"Octopus Energy product, site, or comms.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Hice Wasted Sun en mi tiempo libre, porque ver buen solar tirado me "
"saca de quicio—prefiero enseñar las cifras que tragármelas.\n"
"    No es un producto, web ni comunicación oficial de Octopus Energy.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:187
msgid ""
"\n"
"    I care fiercely about this in part because of my day job as Head of "
"Technology at Octopus Energy Spain—\n"
"    but unless I say otherwise, every sharp word and chart choice here is"
" mine, not my employer’s.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Me importa esto con bronca contenida también por mi trabajo como "
"director de tecnología en Octopus Energy España;\n"
"    salvo que diga lo contrario, cada frase afilada y cada gráfico son "
"cosa mía, no de mi empleador.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:195
msgid ""
"\n"
"  Figures are derived from Red Eléctrica de España data and processed "
"independently for this site;\n"
"  they are not official REE publications or government statistics.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"  Las cifras proceden de datos de Red Eléctrica de España y se procesan "
"de forma independiente para este sitio;\n"
"  no son publicaciones oficiales de REE ni estadísticas gubernamentales.\n"
"  "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:201
msgid ""
"\n"
"  This is a personal side project by Enrique Tasa and is not endorsed by "
"Octopus Energy.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"  Es un proyecto personal de Enrique Tasa y no cuenta con el respaldo de "
"Octopus Energy.\n"
"  "

